         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper we examine cyclic cubic, quartic, and quintic number fields of prime conductor p containing units that bear a special relationship to the classical Gaussian periods: η&lt;sub&gt;j&lt;/sub&gt; - η&lt;sub&gt;j + 1&lt;/sub&gt; + c is a unit for periods η&lt;sub&gt;j&lt;/sub&gt; and c ∈ Z.</p>
          </abstract>
